
git commands

git init    ----- creates a new local repository
git add .    --- complete files addition or file name 
git status    ---- to check status
git commit -m "msg" ---- to commit the changes in the HEAD of local repository
git commit -a -m "msg" --- to commit the changes without staging
git commit --amend -m "newmsg"  ------edit an incoorect commit msg
git log -p --- shows the detailed info of commit and changes made
git branch -v --- show branch names
git branch newbranch (git checkout -b newbranch)--- creates a new branch
git checkout branchname ---- changing the branch name
git merge srcbranch destbranch --- mergering changes to repository
git stash ----  save the local modifications(without commit) and revert back to match the head
git stash apply --- switch to the branch where changes are saved



git remote -v ---- shows the existing remote repository
git clone path ------- creating a working copy in local repository
git fetch origin ---- to fetch the remote repository changes since last cloned
git pull origin --- to fetch and merge  from remote repoistory to working directory
git push origin master --- to push changes to master branch of the remote repository


git config --global user.name "chaithanyaa"
git config --global user.email "chaitanya.1@tcs.com"

git reset HEAD~ ---undo last commit and keep changes
git reset HEAD~2  ----undo last 2 commits and keep changes
git reset --hard HEAD~2 --- undo last 2 commits and discard changes
git reset filename ----remove file from git
git revert specifiedid ----revert specific id commited
git revert HEAD^ ----revert 2nd last commit
git revert -n HEAD  --- undo last commit without creating a revert commit



